This module implements an MPC that handles vertical motions of the CoM.

It contains several classical constraints formulated as tasks such as:
-task_com_height
-task_com_velocity

Two different tasks can be used for the bounds on the CoP location:
-task_cop_bounds (for motions on flat ground without vertical motions of the CoM) -- deprecated
-task_cop_bounds_vertical (for motions with vertical motions of the CoM)

A task ensuring the kinematic feasibility of the motion is:
-task_kinematic
That task relies on a file "task_kinematic.h.in" generated by the python script "tools/python/computeKinematicTask.py" (see description below)

The test scenarios are described in the yaml files. and can be specified as the first option of the test_001 program
e.g. "./build/tests/wpg05/test_001 comanoid_stairs.yaml"
The yaml file must contain a description of the steps to take, the python script "tools/python/computeStepSequence.py"(see description below) can help for that.


**************************
*  ComputeKinematicTask  *
**************************
python3 computeKinematicTask.py --help
usage: computeKinematicTask.py [-h] [--height HEIGHT] [--nIter NITER]
                               [--radius RADIUS]
                               [--center CENTER CENTER CENTER]
                               [--fileName FILENAME] [--plot PLOT]

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --height HEIGHT       Height of the half-space
  --nIter NITER         Number of iteration of the spheres discretization
  --radius RADIUS       Radius of the sphere
  --center CENTER CENTER CENTER
                        Center of the sphere
  --fileName FILENAME   Name of the file where to write the constraint
  --plot PLOT           If True, the constraint polygon is plotted


*************************
*  ComputeStepSequence  *
*************************
python3 computeStepSequence.py --help
usage: computeStepSequence.py [-h] [--CoM0 COM0 COM0 COM0]
                              [--step_width STEP_WIDTH]
                              [--step_duration STEP_DURATION]
                              [--time_step TIME_STEP]
                              [--speed SPEED SPEED SPEED]
                              [--number_of_steps NUMBER_OF_STEPS]
                              [--plot PLOT]

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --CoM0 COM0 COM0 COM0
                        Initial position of the CoM
  --step_width STEP_WIDTH
                        Step width
  --step_duration STEP_DURATION
                        Step duration
  --time_step TIME_STEP
                        Time step
  --speed SPEED SPEED SPEED
                        Walking speed
  --number_of_steps NUMBER_OF_STEPS
                        Number of steps in the simulation
  --plot PLOT           If True, the constraint polygon is plotted

